  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity study was performed during model development to rank the influence of geometric tolerances on the relative hemolysis index; results indicated that impeller tip clearance and inlet angle were the dominant contributors. This screening informed the final operating-point selection but was treated as an internal engineering check rather than a formal uncertainty quantification exercise.",
