    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/dr-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40 Table 1 for Model Risk Level 2. Validation demonstrates mean NIH prediction error of 8.3% within combined uncertainty bounds. RH < 1 criterion satisfied at all 5 operating points. A screening sensitivity study performed during model development confirmed that impeller tip clearance and inlet blade angle are the dominant geometric contributors to hemolysis variation; this information supported operating-point selection and is documented in engineering report ER-CPB-SA-001. The credibility evidence package is assessed as sufficient to support the regulatory submission decision for this Class II CPB device.",
